{"name":"Mathlib.Algebra.ContinuedFractions.Computation.CorrectnessTerminating","instances":[],"imports":["Init","Mathlib.Algebra.ContinuedFractions.Computation.Translations","Mathlib.Algebra.ContinuedFractions.TerminatedStable","Mathlib.Algebra.ContinuedFractions.ContinuantsRecurrence","Mathlib.Order.Filter.AtTopBot","Mathlib.Tactic.FieldSimp"],"declarations":[{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Algebra/ContinuedFractions/Computation/CorrectnessTerminating.lean#L270-L278","name":"GeneralizedContinuedFraction.of_correctness_atTop_of_terminates","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Algebra/ContinuedFractions/Computation/CorrectnessTerminating.html#GeneralizedContinuedFraction.of_correctness_atTop_of_terminates","doc":"If `GeneralizedContinuedFraction.of v` terminates, then its convergents will eventually always\nbe `v`.\n"},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Algebra/ContinuedFractions/Computation/CorrectnessTerminating.lean#L259-L262","name":"GeneralizedContinuedFraction.of_correctness_of_terminates","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Algebra/ContinuedFractions/Computation/CorrectnessTerminating.html#GeneralizedContinuedFraction.of_correctness_of_terminates","doc":"If `GeneralizedContinuedFraction.of v` terminates, then there is `n : ℕ` such that the `n`th\nconvergent is exactly `v`.\n"},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Algebra/ContinuedFractions/Computation/CorrectnessTerminating.lean#L249-L253","name":"GeneralizedContinuedFraction.of_correctness_of_terminatedAt","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Algebra/ContinuedFractions/Computation/CorrectnessTerminating.html#GeneralizedContinuedFraction.of_correctness_of_terminatedAt","doc":"If `GeneralizedContinuedFraction.of v` terminated at step `n`, then the `n`th convergent is\nexactly `v`.\n"},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Algebra/ContinuedFractions/Computation/CorrectnessTerminating.lean#L220-L243","name":"GeneralizedContinuedFraction.of_correctness_of_nth_stream_eq_none","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Algebra/ContinuedFractions/Computation/CorrectnessTerminating.html#GeneralizedContinuedFraction.of_correctness_of_nth_stream_eq_none","doc":"The convergent of `GeneralizedContinuedFraction.of v` at step `n - 1` is exactly `v` if the\n`IntFractPair.stream` of the corresponding continued fraction terminated at step `n`. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Algebra/ContinuedFractions/Computation/CorrectnessTerminating.lean#L106-L213","name":"GeneralizedContinuedFraction.compExactValue_correctness_of_stream_eq_some","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Algebra/ContinuedFractions/Computation/CorrectnessTerminating.html#GeneralizedContinuedFraction.compExactValue_correctness_of_stream_eq_some","doc":"Shows the correctness of `compExactValue` in case the continued fraction\n`GeneralizedContinuedFraction.of v` did not terminate at position `n`. That is, we obtain the\nvalue `v` if we pass the two successive (auxiliary) continuants at positions `n` and `n + 1` as well\nas the fractional part at `IntFractPair.stream n` to `compExactValue`.\n\nThe correctness might be seen more readily if one uses `convergents'` to evaluate the continued\nfraction. Here is an example to illustrate the idea:\n\nLet `(v : ℚ) := 3.4`. We have\n- `GeneralizedContinuedFraction.IntFractPair.stream v 0 = some ⟨3, 0.4⟩`, and\n- `GeneralizedContinuedFraction.IntFractPair.stream v 1 = some ⟨2, 0.5⟩`.\nNow `(GeneralizedContinuedFraction.of v).convergents' 1 = 3 + 1/2`, and our fractional term at\nposition `2` is `0.5`. We hence have `v = 3 + 1/(2 + 0.5) = 3 + 1/2.5 = 3.4`. This computation\ncorresponds exactly to the one using the recurrence equation in `compExactValue`.\n"},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Algebra/ContinuedFractions/Computation/CorrectnessTerminating.lean#L80-L85","name":"GeneralizedContinuedFraction.compExactValue_correctness_of_stream_eq_some_aux_comp","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Algebra/ContinuedFractions/Computation/CorrectnessTerminating.html#GeneralizedContinuedFraction.compExactValue_correctness_of_stream_eq_some_aux_comp","doc":"Just a computational lemma we need for the next main proof. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Algebra/ContinuedFractions/Computation/CorrectnessTerminating.lean#L68-L74","name":"GeneralizedContinuedFraction.compExactValue","kind":"def","docLink":"./Mathlib/Algebra/ContinuedFractions/Computation/CorrectnessTerminating.html#GeneralizedContinuedFraction.compExactValue","doc":"Given two continuants `pconts` and `conts` and a value `fr`, this function returns\n- `conts.a / conts.b` if `fr = 0`\n- `exact_conts.a / exact_conts.b` where `exact_conts = nextContinuants 1 fr⁻¹ pconts conts`\n  otherwise.\n\nThis function can be used to compute the exact value approximated by a continued fraction\n`GeneralizedContinuedFraction.of v` as described in lemma\n`compExactValue_correctness_of_stream_eq_some`.\n"}]}